cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with image processing and computer vision, specifically the task of extracting a video sequence from a single motion-blurred image. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Additionally, the paper addresses the ill-posedness of deblurring, which could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also introduces loss functions that are invariant to the temporal order, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the paper deals with image resampling, which could place it in the cs.GR (Graphics) category.
